(68718, 201854, 0, 1, 'Wicked Soul', '', '2010-04-20 00:00:00', 2010, 19, 1, 5, ' 	\nGamblin'' up in Tucson, happy as can be\nYou were drunk and belligerent, down in Tennessee\nAnd all those things you said that night, you swore you never meant\nBut your lies, they failed to hide, your sinister intent\nI should have known right then what you were doin''\nRealized how you tried to hide the hate that you had brewin''\n\n''Cause you pick and you choose, and you think you''ll never lose\nBut the Lord will see through all that you do\nThey say that there''s a diamond in every piece of coal\nBut I never knew the devil ''til I saw your wicked soul\n\nThen there was that night again, a few months down the road\nI must say I was dismayed by the way things would unfold\nAnd I was in the wrong that night, but when it''s said and done\nI of course lost all remorse when I saw that you had none\nAnd malice is a dress you wear with style\nBut truth be told, that dress gets old, and you''ve worn it for awhile\n\n''Cause you pick and you choose, and you think you''ll never lose\nBut the Lord will see through all that you do\nThey say that there''s a diamond in every piece of coal\nBut I never knew the devil ''til I saw your wicked soul\n\nAnd all this talk of Jesus Christ, and how you had been saved\nAnd how you try not to fall behind the most righteous of ways\n''Cause every sin is equal, that''s what you''d always say\nYou''d use that line to justify your actions every day\nAnd I''ve been told that looks can be deceiving\nBut I''m not sure your scripture was the same one I was reading\n\n''Cause you pick an dyou choose, and you think you''ll never lose\nBut the Lord will see through all tha tyou do\nThey say that there''s a diamond in every piece of coal\nBut I neve rknew the devil ''til I saw your wicked soul', '', 191, '', 'Ty Cooper & Andrew Rogers', 'Ty Cooper', 'Andrew Rogers & Ty Cooper', 'None', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-12-02 00:59:40', '2015-03-12 14:03:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(68719, 201854, 0, 1, '22 Cuts', '', '2010-04-20 00:00:00', 2010, 19, 1, 5, 'When I said I was better, did you believe all my lies?\nWas it hard to see my smile and to look into my eyes?\nAnd when I said I was sick again you had nothing to say\nI can make it through tomorrow if I can make it through today\n\nNow I''m sitting in the bathtub with the curtains all drawn tight\nAnd you call me on the phone to see if I''m doing alright\nAnd I spit back a drunken slur the heartiest of lies\nI made it through those moments but barely made it through last night\n\nThinking about these promises that I had made to you\nAbout all of those silly things I swore I would never do\nLike punishing myself for all the sins that I have done\nI can make it through tomorrow if I can make it to see the sun\n\nSitting in the service watching all the people cry\nAnd eloquently speaking about the man that has just died\nWill they do the same for me or will they just make light\nHe made it through the morning but did not make it through the night\nOh I made it through this morning but I''m not sure about tonight', '', 181, '', 'Ty Cooper', 'Ty Cooper', 'Andrew Rogers & Ty Cooper', 'None', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-12-02 01:02:00', '2015-03-12 14:03:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(68720, 201854, 0, 1, 'Don''t Break My Heart', '', '2010-04-20 00:00:00', 2010, 19, 1, 5, 'Lay here with me, don''t you think about leaving\n''Cause you''re the only thing that keeps me breathing\nEven if the roads we''re on should lead away from us some day\nI''ll gladly take the same one you do any day\n\nJust please don''t break my heart\n''Cause I don''t think it can stand to be torn apart again\nAnd I could give you everything in this life and the next\nAll I''m asking you is just this one request\nDon''t break my heart\n\nThese flower fields, never held such appeal before\nBut when I close my eyes, they''re all I''m seeing anymore\nAnd I could learn to love the south like you do some day\nAs long as your there, it wouldn''t matter anyway\n\nSo please don''t break my heart\n''Cause I don''t think it can stand to be torn apart again\nAnd we can settle down and make a family for two\nThere''s just one thing that I''m asking of you\nDon''t break my heart\n\n', '', 228, '', '', 'Ty Cooper', 'Andrew Rogers & Ty Cooper', 'None', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-12-02 01:03:10', '2015-03-12 14:03:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(68721, 201854, 0, 1, 'Jess'' Song', '', '2010-04-20 00:00:00', 2010, 19, 1, 5, ' 	\nGo over to your apartment sometimes\nAnd watch a silly movie like Neverending Story\nAfterwards we''d play on your computer\nWatch those animations that made you laugh so hard\nAnd I miss your geeky smile\nThick rimmed little glasses, hair up in a pony tail\nDo you remember last october\nYou dressed like bell for Halloween\nA memory so precious to me\n\nAin''t it sad\nThe things we often lose are the best we ever had\nAin''t it so sad\nYou were the best thing, you were the best thing\n\nYou told me that you liked my songs\nJust like prince you said, that meant the world to me you know\nOpened my ears to things I''d never heard\nThe music of David Bowie now ringing in my ears so clear\nAnd those films you made me watch\nLike Hedwig and the Angry Inch, that movie with Johnny Depp and\nNow I''m wondering what I ever did\nTo make you go away, I hope that you come back some day\n\nAin''t it sad\nThe things we often lose are the best we ever had\nAin''t it so sad\nYou were the best thing, you were the best thing\n\nYou told me that you''d never leave my side\nSuch a likely story seeing as your not here with me\nIf I could see you one more time\nI''d tell you not to miss me but I''m pretty sure I''m dead to you\n\nAin''t it sad\nThe things we often lose are the best we ever had\nAin''t it so sad\nYou were the best thing, you were the best thing', '', 173, '', 'Ty Cooper', 'Ty Cooper', 'Andrew Rogers & Ty Cooper', 'None', '', 1, 1, 0, '2013-12-02 01:04:03', '2015-03-12 14:03:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
